parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake system can cause the vehicle to lose braking ability, leading to accidents or near-misses, which can result in injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The brake pedal has to be pushed entirely to the floor to engage
the vehicle fails to decelerate
the brake pedal is soft or spongy
the vehicle shakes or judders when braking.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the parking brake can cause the vehicle to roll or move unexpectedly, leading to accidents or near-misses, which can result in injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The parking brake pad separates from the brake shoe
causing loud squealing or grinding noises
and potentially leading to further damage to the brake system.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Warped brake rotors can cause the vehicle to vibrate or shake when braking, leading to reduced braking performance and potentially causing accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle experiences a bumpy ride
the brake rotor is warped or has a groove cut into it
the vehicle pulls to one side when braking.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The vehicle rolling away unexpectedly can cause accidents or near-misses, which can result in injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle rolls backward or forward when parked on a hill
even when the parking brake is engaged.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of air bags to deploy in the event of a crash can lead to serious injury or death.
symptoms: Air bags do not deploy in a crash
air bag warning light is illuminated
horn is inoperable
air bag emblem has separated.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Air Bag Sensor or Clockspring Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of air bag sensors or clockspring can cause the air bag warning light to illuminate and prevent the air bags from deploying in the event of a crash, leading to serious injury or death.
symptoms: Air bag warning light is illuminated
horn is inoperable
air bag emblem has separated
air bags do not deploy in a crash.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the passenger air bag can cause serious injury or death to the passenger in the event of a crash.
symptoms: Passenger air bag warning light is flashing
passenger air bag does not deploy in a crash
air bag warning light is illuminated.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The inaccurate fuel gauge can cause the vehicle to run out of fuel unexpectedly, leading to stalling, accidents, or stranding the driver.
symptoms: The fuel gauge shows a higher level of fuel than actual
the vehicle stalls or runs out of fuel unexpectedly
the gauge remains stuck at a certain level despite fuel consumption.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The electrical fire can cause damage to the vehicle, surrounding property, and potentially harm occupants.
symptoms: Sudden
unexplained fire under the dashboard
destruction of the vehicle and surrounding property
no warning signs or symptoms prior to the fire.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the throttle actuator and ECM can cause the vehicle to stall, lose power, or accelerate unexpectedly, leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: Service light and slip light illumination
vehicle stalling
loss of power
sudden acceleration
failure to accelerate.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the exhaust system can cause damage to surrounding components, such as wiring harnesses, and lead to loss of critical vehicle systems, including ABS, traction control, and fuel pump.
symptoms: Rusted flange connecting tailpipe to muffler
hot exhaust melting wiring harness
loss of ABS
ECM
traction control
fuel pump
and other critical systems.
